# =====================================================================
# .gitignore for the LINDA-STUFF repo
# =====================================================================
# Philosophy:
#   - Track the "work-product" (notebook, helpers, KB, sidecars, docs).
#   - Don't track raw datasets (datalad-installed; reproducible).
#   - Don't track derivatives (regenerable from raw + code; large).
#   - Don't track caches (atlases, HD-BET intermediates).
# Every machine should re-install the dataset via datalad and re-run
# the segmentation cell to recreate derivatives.
# =====================================================================

# --- Datasets (datalad-installed; reinstall on each machine) ---------
ds004884/
# Any other OpenNeuro-style raw dataset folders you might add later
ds[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]/

# --- Anatomical inputs (symlinks/copies of datalad data) -------------
# Keep the folder structure for reference but skip the heavy NIfTIs.
ds004884_anat/sub-*/ses-*/anat/*_T1w.nii.gz
ds004884_anat/**/anat/*_T1w.json

# --- Derivatives (regenerated by re-running segmentation) ------------
ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/sub-*/ses-*/anat/linda/*.nii.gz
ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/sub-*/ses-*/anat/linda/*.RData
ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/sub-*/ses-*/anat/linda/*.mat
ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/sub-*/ses-*/anat/linda/*.txt
ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/sub-*/ses-*/anat/linda/_linda_original/

# IMPORTANT exception: keep the QC sidecars + the qc_summary aggregated CSV.
# These are small and represent your epistemic decisions — they MUST travel.
!ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/**/*.qc.json
!ds004884_anat/derivatives/lesion_mask/qc_summary.csv

# --- HD-BET workspace (intermediate; regenerated on re-run) ----------
_hdbet_work/
**/_hdbet_work/

# --- Atlas cache (re-downloaded by nilearn / atlas loader cell) ------
atlases/

# --- QC round-trip area (per-subject scratch) ------------------------
qc_edits/

# --- Anat inputs leftover from early build attempts ------------------
anat_inputs/

# --- Mac, editor, Python noise ---------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.ipynb_checkpoints/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- Virtual environment ---------------------------------------------
.venv/
venv/

# --- nilearn cache outside our atlases/ folder, just in case ---------
.nilearn_data/

# --- Aphasia-KB scratch ----------------------------------------------
# Track regions/, impairments/, therapies/, drafts/, examples/.
# Don't track source PDFs (too large + may be copyrighted; keep them
# locally per machine). DO track annotated PDFs — they're the
# reviewer's primary verification tool and must travel between
# machines (~1–2 MB each, agent-generated, not copyrighted).
aphasia-kb/papers/*.pdf
!aphasia-kb/papers/*_annotated.pdf
!aphasia-kb/papers/*_annotated_v[0-9].pdf
aphasia-kb/__pycache__/
aphasia-kb/_neurosynth_cache/
